        adaptedContent: "## Stop Deploying Software. Start Deploying Confidence.\n\n**The hook:** Every DevOps team has a war story about The Deploy That Broke Everything. Apollo makes that story impossible.\n\n### Platform-Native Angles\n\n**LinkedIn (B2B):**\n\"A single failed deployment to an air-gapped site costs $50-200K. Apollo eliminates 95% of those failures. The math is obvious.\"\n\n**Twitter/X (developers):**\n\"What if your deployment system was smarter than your best SRE? Apollo evaluates 50+ constraints and rolls back faster than you can open a terminal. No internet required.\"\n\n**Blog (thought leadership):**\nThe future of deployment isn't faster CI/CD. It's autonomous systems that never panic, never forget a dependency, and never deploy on a Friday at 4:59 PM.\n\n### Campaign Arc\n\n**Day 1 (curiosity):** Customer war story + tease\n**Day 2 (conversion):** Live demo video — deploy → constraint check → rollback in 30 sec\n**Day 3 (credibility):** Technical deep-dive blog\n\n### One-Line Pitch\n\n\"Apollo is autopilot for software deployment — it flies the plane, checks the weather, and lands safely even when the tower goes dark.\"",
