        adaptedContent: "## \"We Found 847 Defects Last Quarter That Humans Missed.\"\n\nThat's the LinkedIn headline. That's the hook. That's the entire top-of-funnel strategy.\n\n### Platform Playbook\n\n**LinkedIn (manufacturing decision-makers):**\n\"Our inspectors are great. They catch 92% of defects. But 8% of 2.4 million boards is 192,000 defective units per year. We added AI vision. Now we catch 99.7%. The 847 saves from last quarter alone paid for the system 3x over.\"\n\n**Twitter/X (AI/tech audience):**\n\"Running ResNet-50 on a Jetson at 15 FPS to inspect PCBs. 99.7% detection rate. The interesting part? Humans now only review the ambiguous 3%. Their job got better, not eliminated. 🧵\"\n\n**YouTube/Demo video:**\nSplit-screen: left side shows human inspector under magnification, right side shows AI overlay highlighting defects in real-time. Same board, same defects — AI catches one the human missed. 30 seconds. No narration needed.\n\n### Campaign Arc\n\n**Day 1:** \"847 defects caught\" stat + factory floor photo\n**Day 2:** 30-sec split-screen demo video\n**Day 3:** \"AI didn't replace our inspectors — it made them better\" human interest story\n\n### The Pitch in 10 Words\n\n\"AI catches what humans miss. Humans judge what AI can't.\"",
