        adaptedContent: "## Tariff Classification Engine: Technical Review\n\n### The Data Problem\n\nUS-China tariff compliance requires classifying every imported component to a 10-digit HTS code. For a company importing 5,000 SKUs, that's 5,000 classification decisions, each with legal liability.\n\n**Current automated approaches:**\n- **Rule-based systems:** Map product descriptions to HTS codes via keyword matching. Fast, brittle. Fails on novel products or ambiguous descriptions. ~75% accuracy.\n- **ML classification:** Fine-tuned BERT on CBP ruling database (~50K labeled rulings). ~91% accuracy but confidence-calibration is poor — the model is confidently wrong on edge cases.\n- **Gaia's approach:** Hybrid — ML primary classifier + rule-based guardrails + mandatory human review for low-confidence classifications. Confidence threshold: if ML probability < 0.85, route to human. This catches the dangerous failure mode: high-confidence misclassification.\n\n### Architecture Trade-offs\n\n**Chose recall over precision for tariff classification.** A false positive (flagging a product that doesn't need review) costs time. A false negative (misclassifying a product) costs penalties — potentially 4x the duty owed plus criminal liability. The system is deliberately conservative.\n\n**No real-time classification.** Batch processing with 24-hour SLA. Trade-off: importers can't get instant classification, but the system has time for multi-model ensemble and human review. Right call for regulatory compliance.\n\n### What Could Break\n\n- **Regulatory drift** — tariff rates change faster than the training data updates\n- **Adversarial descriptions** — suppliers gaming product descriptions to avoid tariffs\n- **Cross-border complexity** — rules of origin for assembled goods with components from multiple countries\n\n### Verdict\n\nThe hybrid approach is the right architecture for a domain where false negatives have legal consequences. The 0.85 confidence threshold is reasonable. Missing: adversarial robustness testing and a regulatory change detection pipeline.",
